      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2025-05-25T19:46:39.933Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hi Thomas, thanks!!! I can\u2019t read all of this thread below (in French it looks like) but it looks like your bike does not work in ERG mode in Zwift either so that would be a problem with the bike.  We have slope mode (you can click on slope and up down to see if that works, sounds like it does in zwift) but you still have to control your power manually.</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox discoursetopic\" data-onebox-src=\"https://forums.zwift.com/t/bodytone-smb1-v2-informations-resistances-automatic/553409/4\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/49580793fa0d2547f1ef801be5d9d1dbbafa9329.png\" class=\"site-icon\" data-dominant-color=\"F69768\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://forums.zwift.com/t/bodytone-smb1-v2-informations-resistances-automatic/553409/4\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"04:55PM - 29 August 2021\">Zwift Forums \u2013 29 Aug 21</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/b/ba8bd2bdc60d75aead93bb2d4fe71abb793ddd3b_2_500x500.png\" class=\"thumbnail onebox-avatar\" data-dominant-color=\"D95C26\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\">\n\n<div class=\"title-wrapper\">\n  <h3><a href=\"https://forums.zwift.com/t/bodytone-smb1-v2-informations-resistances-automatic/553409/4\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bodytone SMB1 V2 - Informations resistances automatic</a></h3>\n  <div class=\"topic-category\">\n      <span class=\"badge-wrapper bullet\">\n        <span class=\"badge-category-bg\" style=\"background-color: #FC6719;\"></span>\n        <span class=\"badge-category clear-badge\">\n          <span class=\"category-name\">General Discussion</span>\n        </span>\n      </span>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n  <p>I have the Bodytone SMB1 V2.  You may link the \u201cPower Source\u201d, the \u201cCadence\u201d and the \u201cControllable\u201d options from Zwift. With these settings:   In \u201cFree Ride\u201d mode: Zwift will control the resistance on the bike, you will feel the resistance changes...</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n",
