      "cooked": "<p>Alex, thanks for your response. I share your view about slope being a resistance proxy with different units.  I\u2019m going to repeat my experiments under more controlled conditions to aid comparisons and help others repeat them if they wish.  In the meantime, I need a clarification; when you write \u201cuse slope mode and shift to set power targets\u201d, do you mean erg mode shifts to slope mode at the hi-intensity interval start, and then slope shifts back to erg mode at the interval end?<br>\nMarty</p>",
